{{Top|canon=Talzzi}}
{{Quote|We are Talz, and all Talz are one. Talz remind ourselves of this always. Our language is not your concern.|Armaruk|<ref name="Jedi Master on Ice">{{TORcite|type=class|Sith Warrior|Jedi Master on Ice|Hoth}}</ref>}}
'''Talz''' was the native [[Language/Legends|language]] of the [[Talz/Legends|Talz]] species from [[Alzoc III/Legends|Alzoc III]]. It was mainly composed of buzzes and chirps, with variable pitch being an essential feature.<ref name="u">''[[Ultimate Alien Anthology]]''</ref>

The Talz throat and proboscis structure made them unable to speak most languages of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] except for their own. Most Talz were not fluent in [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Basic]] and had no understanding of it. As Talz language was not very well-known outside Alzoc III, [[Protocol droid/Legends|protocol droids]] were usually not fluent in that language, although they could easily be programmed to translate it.<ref name="u" />

==Words==
